@baseUrl = http://localhost:4000
@scenarioVersion = {{$timestamp}}

### Cadastro com dados validos -> 201 sem corpo
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Maria da Silva",
  "email": "maria.{{scenarioVersion}}@example.com",
  "password": "Strong@123"
}

### Cadastro com e-mail ja existente -> 409 (mesma versao do cenario anterior)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Maria da Silva",
  "email": "maria.{{scenarioVersion}}@example.com",
  "password": "Strong@123"
}

### Cadastro com senha fraca -> 422
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Maria da Silva",
  "email": "maria.fraca.{{scenarioVersion}}@example.com",
  "password": "123456"
}

### Cadastro com senha comum na blacklist -> 422
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Maria da Silva",
  "email": "maria.comum.{{scenarioVersion}}@example.com",
  "password": "123456"
}

### Cadastro com nome invalido -> 422
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "M4",
  "email": "maria.nome.{{scenarioVersion}}@example.com",
  "password": "Strong@123"
}

### Cadastro com email invalido -> 422
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Maria da Silva",
  "email": "nao-e-um-email",
  "password": "Strong@123"
}

### Cadastro com multiplos campos invalidos -> 422 com varios itens em errors[]
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "",
  "email": "nao-e-um-email",
  "password": "123456"
}
